Word Tokenization (Complexity: Simple)¶

In [8]:
%%time
stop_words=set(stopwords.words('english'))
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
punc_trans = str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation)

sentence_re = r'(?:(?:[A-Z])(?:.[A-Z])+.?)|(?:\w+(?:-\w+)*)|(?:\$?\d+(?:.\d+)?%?)|(?:...|)(?:[][.,;"\'?():-_`])'

CPU times: user 2.8 ms, sys: 12.3 ms, total: 15.1 ms
Wall time: 32.1 ms
In [9]:
def generate_words(text):
    
    try:
        text.lower()
    except AttributeError:
        return ''
#         return [] # <- turn column into string
    
    text = text.translate(punc_trans)  # remove punctuations
    
    word_tokens = nltk.regexp_tokenize(text,sentence_re) # tokenizing
    
    return word_tokens
def generate_words_sp(text):
    text = text['comments']
    try:
        text.lower()
    except AttributeError:
        return ''
#         return [] # <- turn column into string
    
    text = text.translate(punc_trans)  # remove punctuations
    
    word_tokens = nltk.regexp_tokenize(text,sentence_re) # tokenizing
    
    return word_tokens

Multiproccessed¶

In [16]:
for index,data in enumerate(running_speed['word_tokenization']['data']['pandas']):
    for core_count in running_speed['word_tokenization']['parallel']:
        st = time.time()
        word_tokens = Parallel(n_jobs=core_count)(delayed(generate_words)(x) for x in data['comments'])
        et = time.time()
        running_speed['word_tokenization']['parallel'][core_count][index] = et-st
        print('time:' + str(et-st))

Phrases Generation and POS tagging (Complexity: Moderate)¶

In [13]:
grammar = r"""
NBAR:
    {<NN.*|JJ>*<NN.*>}  # phrases of nouns or adjectives then Nouns

NP:
    {<NBAR>}  # this phrase
    {<NBAR><IN><NBAR>}  # Between in/of/and

VVV:
    {<V.*>}  # all verbs we wrap them up
"""
grammer_ext = nltk.RegexpParser(grammar)

tag_translator = {
    "J": wordnet.ADJ,
    "N": wordnet.NOUN,
    "V": wordnet.VERB,
    "R": wordnet.ADV
}
In [14]:
def filter_trees(tree):
    # gives leaves if see tree
    for subtree in tree.subtrees(filter = lambda t: t.label()=='NP' or t.label() == 'VVV'):
        yield subtree.leaves()
        
def generate_phrases_and_lemmatize(word_tokens):
    
    pos_tokens = nltk.tag.pos_tag(word_tokens) # POS
    if len(pos_tokens) == 0:
        return []
    tree = grammer_ext.parse(pos_tokens,trace=0) #apply new grammer
    terms = [ \
        [ lemmatizer.lemmatize(w,tag_translator.get(t[0],tag_translator['N'])) for w,t in leaf if not w in stop_words ] \
             for leaf in filter_trees(tree) \
    ]  # filter pos with np and vvv and lemmatize according to context
    
    terms = [
        ' '.join(term) 
        for term in terms if len(term)
    ]
    
    return terms

# extracted_phrases = Parallel(n_jobs=10)(delayed(generate_phrases)(text) for text in reviews_df.word_tokens.iloc[:10])

Multiproccessed¶

In [27]:
%%time
skip_1mil = True
for index,data in enumerate(running_speed['phrases_generation']['data']['pandas']):
    if skip_1mil:
        skip_1mil = False
        continue
    for core_count in running_speed['phrases_generation']['parallel']:
        st = time.time()
        extracted_phrases = Parallel(n_jobs=core_count)(delayed(generate_phrases_and_lemmatize)(x) for x in data['word_tokens'])
        et = time.time()
        running_speed['phrases_generation']['parallel'][core_count][index] = et-st
        print('time:' + str(et-st))

Sentiment Analysis (Complexity: High)¶

In [36]:
def sentiment_analysis(phrases):
    analyzer = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer() 
    senti_list_temp = []
    for i in phrases:
        vs = analyzer.polarity_scores(i)
        senti_list_temp.append((i, vs))
        senti_list_temp = [w for w in senti_list_temp if w]
    sentiment_list  = []
    hotel_rating = 0
    review_length = 0
    for j in senti_list_temp:
        first = j[0]
        second = j[1]
        sentence_length = len(first.split(' '))
        for (k,v) in second.items():
            if k == 'compound':
                if v < 0.0:
                    sentiment_list.append((first, "-"))
                    hotel_rating += sentence_length * v
                    review_length += sentence_length
                elif v == 0.0:
                    sentiment_list.append((first, "0"))
                else:
                    sentiment_list.append((first, "+"))
                    hotel_rating += sentence_length * v
                    review_length += sentence_length
    if review_length != 0:
        hotel_rating = hotel_rating / review_length
    return (sentiment_list, hotel_rating)

Process but keep pos context for futher testing¶

In [55]:
def filter_trees_keep_pos(tree):
    # gives leaves if see tree
    for subtree in tree.subtrees(filter = lambda t: t.label()=='NP' or t.label() == 'VVV'):
        yield (subtree.leaves(),subtree.label())
        
def generate_phrases_and_lemmatize_labelling(word_tokens):
    
    pos_tokens = nltk.tag.pos_tag(word_tokens) # POS
    if len(pos_tokens) == 0:
        return []
    tree = grammer_ext.parse(pos_tokens,trace=0) #apply new grammer
    terms = [ \
        ([ (lemmatizer.lemmatize(w,tag_translator.get(t[0],tag_translator['N'])),t) for w,t in leaf if not w in stop_words ],pos ) \
             for leaf,pos in filter_trees_keep_pos(tree) \
    ]  # filter pos with np and vvv and lemmatize according to context
    
    terms = [
        term
        for term in terms if len(term)
    ]
    
    # produce dict 
    res = {}
    for term in terms:
        
    
    return terms

In [46]:
def sentiment_analysis(phrases):
    analyzer = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer() 
    senti_list_temp = []
    for i in phrases:
        vs = analyzer.polarity_scores(i)
        senti_list_temp.append((i, vs))
        senti_list_temp = [w for w in senti_list_temp if w]
    sentiment_list  = []
    hotel_rating = 0
    review_length = 0
    for j in senti_list_temp:
        first = j[0]
        second = j[1]
        sentence_length = len(first.split(' '))
        for (k,v) in second.items():
            if k == 'compound':
                if v < 0.0:
                    sentiment_list.append((first,v, "-"))
                    hotel_rating += sentence_length * v
                    review_length += sentence_length
                elif v == 0.0:
                    sentiment_list.append((first,v, "0"))
                else:
                    sentiment_list.append((first,v, "+"))
                    hotel_rating += sentence_length * v
                    review_length += sentence_length
    if review_length != 0:
        hotel_rating = hotel_rating / review_length
    return (sentiment_list, hotel_rating)
